<p>Sweeping up the palm tree lined avenue to your first sight of the beautiful hotel, you are greeted by the smiling staff with a personalised drink of coconut water and a flower garland. I have to tell you that I teared up at how lovely this greeting was after a long journey to get there, so make sure your mascara is waterproof!</p>

<p><img src="/images/travel/melia-bali/melia-bali-3-w1200.jpg" alt="melia-bali-3-w1200.jpg" /></p>

<p>The hotel is a resort set in beautiful landscaped gardens with the option of private villas with your own pool. Our stone villa â€“ Villa Laksamana - with its traditional thatched roof and azure pool, was stunning.</p>

